    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3833332" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8317242728703501438">R. K. Narayan is an absolute favourite of mine and some of his works are undoubtedly masterpieces.<br/>His The English Teacher is the third part of Narayan&apos;s trilogy after Malgudi Days and The Bachelor of Arts (for review, you could check out sandyi.blogspot.com.<br/><br/> The first part of this particular book is brilliant and extremely touching but the second part moves into very unexpected territory, leaving one a bit confused. Yet, if you are a Narayan fan, I would still go ahead and recommend this book to</span>
  <span id="freeText8317242728703501438" style="display:none">R. K. Narayan is an absolute favourite of mine and some of his works are undoubtedly masterpieces.<br />His The English Teacher is the third part of Narayan's trilogy after Malgudi Days and The Bachelor of Arts (for review, you could check out sandyi.blogspot.com.<br /><br /> The first part of this particular book is brilliant and extremely touching but the second part moves into very unexpected territory, leaving one a bit confused. Yet, if you are a Narayan fan, I would still go ahead and recommend this book to you.<br /></span>
